						               													<description>A trivia card game. There are three decks of cards, each contain a list of numbered facts, some true ('no bull') and some false ('bullshit'). Players take turns to be read one fact from a card, chosen by a die roll, and must decide if that fact is true or false. If they are correct they keep the card used, if they are wrong the card is returned to the bottom of the deck. Confident players may 'bet' 1, 2 or 3 cards on their answer; if they are correct they will receive this many extra cards from the current deck, if they are wrong they must pay that many cards back to the deck.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Once each deck is exhausted, the player with the most cards from that deck in front of them is declared the winner of that deck, and play moves to the next deck. Once all three decks have been worked through, the game ends. If any player was declared the winner of at least two of the three decks, they win the game. Note that this may not be the player who won the most cards over the whole game. If no player was the winner of at least two of the three decks, then whoever has the most cards in front of them wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
